    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized field access in M2AP/X2AP ID allocation\n\n### Summary\nThe M2AP and X2AP ID allocation functions were not properly initializing all fields in the allocated entries. This caused undefined behavior when accessing uninitialized pointers and state fields, leading to potential crashes during handover procedures.\n\nThe issue manifests when the system attempts to access the `target` pointer or `state` field of an allocated ID entry that hasn't been fully initialized. In some cases, this results in segmentation faults during handover request processing.\n\nThis fix ensures all fields are properly initialized to known values during allocation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_ids.c`: Added initialization of all struct fields in `m2ap_allocate_new_id()`\n- `openair2/X2AP/x2ap_ids.c`: Added initialization of all struct fields in `x2ap_allocate_new_id()`\n- Both files now include `<stddef.h>` for proper NULL definition\n\n"
}